VALUES ('B2_U25_B1_I1', 'ingles-b2-U25', 1, 'fill_blanks', 'Fill in the blanks with the correct form of the word provided in parentheses.

Base words: (1) ACT, (2) COMMUNICATE, (3) HEALTH, (4) COLOR, (5) NATIVE', '{"prompt_es":"Fill in the blanks with the correct form of the word provided in parentheses.\n\nBase words: (1) ACT, (2) COMMUNICATE, (3) HEALTH, (4) COLOR, (5) NATIVE","mastery_tag":"vocabulary:b2-idiomatic","main_text":"Idioms are an important part of the English language. They often (1)___ (ACT) in a way that is not literal. Understanding idioms can greatly improve your (2)___ (COMMUNICATE) skills. For example, when someone says they are ''feeling under the weather,'' they mean they are not (3)___ (HEALTH) or they are sick. Using idiomatic expressions can make your speech more (4)___ (COLOR) and engaging. Additionally, it helps you to sound more like a (5)___ (NATIVE) speaker.","correct_answer":["ACTS","COMMUNICATION","HEALTHY","COLORFUL","NATIVES"],"explanation":"(1) undefined\n(2) undefined\n(3) undefined\n(4) undefined\n(5) undefined","complexity":3,"concept_tags":["vocabulary","idiomatic","unit"]}')
